### Lecturer Management API Tests

### 1. Create a new lecturer
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/lecturers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Dr. Sarah",
  "lastName": "Johnson",
  "email": "sarah.johnson@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "specialization": "Computer Science",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "hireDate": "2020-01-15"
}

### 2. Create another lecturer
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/lecturers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Prof. Michael",
  "lastName": "Brown",
  "email": "michael.brown@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "specialization": "Mathematics",
  "phoneNumber": "+1987654321",
  "hireDate": "2019-09-01"
}

### 3. Get lecturer by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/lecturers/1

### 4. Get all courses taught by a lecturer
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/lecturers/1/courses?page=0&size=10

### 5. Get all students enrolled in lecturer's courses
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/lecturers/1/students?page=0&size=10

### 6. Get students for a specific course taught by lecturer
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/lecturers/1/courses/1/students?page=0&size=10

### 7. Get lecturer statistics
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/lecturers/1/stats

### 8. Test getting non-existent lecturer (should fail)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/lecturers/999

### 9. Test creating lecturer with duplicate email (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/lecturers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Duplicate",
  "lastName": "Lecturer",
  "email": "sarah.johnson@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "specialization": "Physics"
}

### 10. Test creating lecturer with invalid data (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/lecturers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "",
  "lastName": "",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "123"
}
